adminPause(uint256).details: adminPause pauses this contract. Only pause role or default admin role can access this function.

params.flags: flags variable is used for pausing this contract.

createFixedLocksOnBehalfOfUserByAdmin((u.details: Admin can create a lock on behalf of a user without early withdrawal

createStream(uint256,uint256).details: This function creates a stream and makes it live. Only the Stream Owner is able to call this function.      Stream Owner is set while proposing a stream

emergencyUnlockAndWithdraw().details: In case of emergency, unlock your tokens and withdraw all your position

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

initializeMainStream(address,uint256[],u.details: The function is callable only once, and it can be done only with admin,       which at initial setup is Multisig

initializeStaking(address,address,addres.details: initialize the contract and deploys the first stream of rewardsinitializable only once due to stakingInitialised flag

params._admin: the owner and manager of the main token stream
params._vault: The Vault address to store main token and rewards tokens
params._weight: Weighting coefficient for shares and penalties

proposeStream(address,address,uint256,ui.details: An admin of the staking contract can allowlist (propose) a stream. Allowlisting of the stream provides the option for the stream owner (presumably the issuing party of a specific token) to deposit some ERC-20 tokens on the staking contract and potentially get in return some main tokens immediately.

params.maxDepositAmount: The upper amount of the tokens that should be deposited by stream owner
params.rewardToken: the address of the ERC-20 tokens to be deposited in the stream
params.scheduleRewards: remaining rewards to be delivered at the beginning of each scheduled interval.  Last element is always zero. First value (in scheduleRewards) from array is supposed to be a total amount of rewards for stream.
params.scheduleTimes: timestamp denoting the start of each scheduled interval. Last element is the end of the stream.
params.streamOwner: only this account will be able to launch a stream
params.tau: the tau is (pending release period) for this stream (e.g one day)

removeStream(uint256,address).details: A stream can be removed after all the rewards pending have been withdrawn.      Stream can be removed by the Stream Manager which is Multisig at time of deployment.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setMaxLockPositions(uint256).details: This allows for setting up maximum lock positions.      Only admin which is Multisig at deployment can call this

setMinimumLockPeriod(uint256).details: This allows for setting up minimum locking period.      Only admin which is Multisig at deployment can call this

updateVault(address).details: Vault can be updated only if the contract is at paused state.      Only Admin that is, Multisig at the time of deployment can update Vault

withdrawPenalty().details: Penalty accrued due to early unlocking can be withdrawn to some address, most likely the treasury.      Address with TREASURY_ROLE can access this function, which is Multisig at time of deployment

emergencyUnlockAndWithdraw().notice: This function neglects all the rewardsThis can be executed only if the contract is at paused state.This function can only be called if VaultContract is not compromised and vault is not at paused state.

initializeStaking(address,address,addres.notice: By calling this function, the deployer of this contract must make sure that the Rewards amount was deposited to the treasury contract before initializing of the default Stream

weight().notice: Weighting coefficient for shares and penalties
